<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Nicolas Tabet, a systems-focused engineer working in operating systems, C, and infrastructure."
>
  <div class="prose">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>
      I'm a systems-focused engineer. What I like most is working low in the
      stack: operating systems, memory, processes, the boundary with the kernel,
      and the networking underneath. I would rather build a thing from scratch
      and understand it than take it on faith, which is how most of my projects
      start.
    </p>
    <p>
      I just finished a double major in Computer Science and Mathematics at
      Purdue. For two years I was a TA and course developer for CS 240, its
      introductory C course, and I spent time in the SecArch lab using language
      models to explore the design space of branch predictors. This fall I'm
      starting Columbia's MSCS on the software systems track.
    </p>
    <p>
      Outside of school I've built for people who actually use the software. I
      led the platform for a delivery startup, and interned at Aboard AI, Rix,
      and Murex across New York, London, and Paris. I also run a small homelab
      that hosts my own services, including this site.
    </p>
    <p>
      I grew up between the US, Paris, and Lebanon, and I work in English,
      French, and Arabic. For the full timeline and the details, here's
      my <a href="https://public.nicolastabet.com/files/resume.pdf">résumé</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
